id: pmc-8t9f
title: Relax changelog title escaping for readable Markdown
description: "Fix downstream pm-cli pm-3299: generated changelog entry titles over-escape harmless GitHub Markdown characters, including parentheses and intra-word underscores such as EXTENSION_AUTHOR_CONTRACTS. Keep strict escaping for IDs, metadata, links, and body previews while using title-context escaping for item titles."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: changelog,downstream-pm-cli,markdown
created_at: "2026-06-20T03:11:44.884Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-29T14:19:30.928Z"
author: codex-implementation-agent
parent: pmc-4279
resolution: "Title-context changelog escaping preserves complete backtick-delimited inline-code spans, escapes unmatched backticks in normal title text, and still escapes surrounding prose punctuation."
expected_result: "Complete inline-code commands keep their Markdown punctuation readable, while unmatched backticks and normal bracket/underscore prose remain escaped."
actual_result: "Regression coverage now verifies command brackets stay literal inside inline code, surrounding underscore prose is escaped, unmatched backticks are escaped, and npm test passed with 108 tests."
comments[9]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-20T03:12:12.682Z",codex-implementation-agent,"Evidence: implemented title-context escaping for changelog item titles; npm run typecheck passed; npm test passed (89 tests); npm run audit:prod found 0 vulnerabilities; npm run pack:dry-run succeeded. changelog:check intentionally pending until this item is closed and CHANGELOG.md regenerated."
  "2026-06-20T03:13:39.236Z",codex-implementation-agent,"Evidence: npm run release:check passed after full-history changelog regeneration. Manual temp smoke passed in /tmp/pm-changelog-title-escape-QkBnRg: local package installed with pm install <repo> --project, generated CHANGELOG.md contains 'Fix EXTENSION_AUTHOR_CONTRACTS docs (actual 1.4.0)' without escaped underscores or parentheses."
  "2026-06-20T03:15:46.237Z",codex-implementation-agent,"Final evidence: npm run release:check passed after adding pmc-licw and regenerating CHANGELOG.md; title escaping regression remains green and full package changelog check reports up to date."
  "2026-06-29T13:54:20.718Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation note: downstream pm-cli PR #402 exposed the remaining title-escaping gap: item titles containing markdown inline code render as escaped backticks. Patched src/generator.ts to preserve literal backticks in title-context escaping while keeping strict escaping for other structural characters; added test/generator.test.ts coverage for  inline code. Verification so far: npm test passed (107 tests)."
  "2026-06-29T13:54:32.824Z",claude-code-agent,"Correction to previous note: the added regression specifically covers the item title text \"Dogfood: pm-kanban registers kanbanProfile so `pm profile apply kanban` works\" and asserts the generated changelog preserves the inline-code backticks instead of rendering escaped backticks."
  "2026-06-29T14:13:03.273Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up: cubic identified that preserving backticks was not enough because Markdown punctuation inside an inline-code span could still be escaped. Updated title escaping to preserve complete backtick-delimited spans and escape only surrounding prose. Verification so far: npm test passed with 107 tests."
  "2026-06-29T14:14:48.422Z",claude-code-agent,"Final follow-up evidence: pm test pmc-8t9f --run --progress passed all 5 linked checks; npm run release:check passed, including typecheck, 107 tests, npm audit --omit=dev with 0 vulnerabilities, npm pack --dry-run, and changelog:check."
  "2026-06-29T14:18:28.502Z",claude-code-agent,"Gemini follow-up: unmatched backticks outside complete inline-code spans are escaped again, while complete backtick spans are preserved. Added a regression for an unmatched backtick before bracketed text. Verification so far: npm test passed with 108 tests."
  "2026-06-29T14:19:30.726Z",claude-code-agent,"Final Gemini follow-up evidence: pm test pmc-8t9f --run --progress passed all 5 linked checks; npm run release:check passed with 108 tests, 0 production audit vulnerabilities, pack dry-run, and changelog:check."
